Project Overview:
This project focuses on forecasting monthly export volumes of U.S. coking coal using a neuro-fuzzy approach based on the ANFIS (Adaptive Neuro-Fuzzy Inference System) framework.
The workflow includes time series analysis, autocorrelation assessment, seasonal pattern identification, data preprocessing, ANFIS model training, and forecasting accuracy evaluation.

Tools:
- MATLAB
- ANFIS Editor
- Fuzzy Logic Toolbox
- Time Series Analysis

Methods Applied:
- Autocorrelation Function (ACF) Analysis
- Lag Selection
- Seasonal Feature Engineering
- Training and Test Data Split (5:1)
- Neuro-Fuzzy Modeling (ANFIS)
- Forecast Accuracy Evaluation

Project Workflow:
1. Analysis of historical monthly export data.
2. Identification of significant lag variables using autocorrelation analysis.
3. Consideration of quarterly and yearly seasonal components.
4. Preparation of training and testing datasets.
5. Training of a neuro-fuzzy forecasting model.
6. Evaluation of forecasting performance on unseen data.

Results:
The project demonstrates the application of neuro-fuzzy systems for time series forecasting and evaluates the impact of historical observations and seasonal patterns on prediction accuracy.
